node.text:
Chiron Retrograde ⊹⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ July 15 - December 19
Chiron the asteroid that rules our deepest wounds and healing has now stationed retrograde in the sign of Aries and will be for the next 5 months, this karmic transit is here to guide you towards profound healing, a time to free yourself from wounds and blockages that have been holding you back and keeping you in cycles of self sabotage and generational patterning. 

Chiron is one of the biggest spiritual teachers in astrology. Chiron illuminates your deepest spiritual and emotional wounds, to show you where healing needs to be done. 

This is the perfect time to start doing the work and healing your inner child, so in light of this powerful cycle I have just launched my “healing the inner child” guide and workbook, which is filled with information on inner child wounds and guides you on a journey of healing those wounds. I have also discounted this workbook 50% off for this first week of this Chiron retrograde, download your copy and begin your healing ✨

node.text:
For those who were born with their natal Saturn in Aquarius you are currently going through your first Saturn Return (this may be you if you were born between the years 1991 - 1994 check your birth chart, or you can comment your birthday below and I will let you know) ༄ 

Saturn Returns have a bad rep, because they are known for really shaking things in your life up, for throwing some intense lessons your way, but it’s all for a bigger purpose. To me Saturn returns are a beautiful time of deep learning, lots of reflection and realisations and of course those big life changes, that can be scary, but are ultimately happening for you, not to you. 

Instead of fearing this transit, look at Saturn as your greatest teacher. Illuminating the parts of your life that aren’t serving you any longer. When you shift your focus to this, seeing your Saturn return as a positive moment in time of your life, you won’t fall victim to any tough lessons that come with this transit. 
When things arise that cause a reaction in you, take a step and ask yourself – what is this trying to teach me?

If you are currently going through your SR and would like some more guidance on this time I have a digital guide which you can download on my website under the guides and ebooks section that goes into more depth on the specifics of having your Saturn Return in Aquarius.

node.text:
MERCURY ENTERS CANCER ⊹⁣ On Monday Mercury the planet of the mind has moved into the emotional sign of Cancer. When Mercury sits in this beautiful and nurturing water sign our minds tend to shift and align more with this soft, emotional, deep energy and while this shift does make us prone to being more sensitive, it also gives us this homely energy to be able to sit with ourselves and really tap into our feelings and how we process through them. ⁣
⁣
Remember to hold space for your emotions, be truly present with what you’re feeling. Each emotion that comes through you is a message, that is trying to tell you something. No emotion is wrong. All emotions are needed and valid.⁣
⁣
Instead of pushing down uncomfortable feelings and emotions, when these arise ask yourself what is this feeling trying to tell me?

node.text:
New Moon in Cancer ⚘ July 9 / 10
New moons are a time to honour the things we have gone through and set new intentions and goals.

This New Moon in Cancer is all about self love, trusting your intuition, connecting to the divine feminine, holding space for your emotions, reflection and realignment, family, home life and self care rituals. 

During this moon emotions are heightened, so it is the perfect time to retreat within and take the this time to yourself, for yourself. 

Journal prompts for New Moon in Cancer:
When my emotions arise how do I handle them?
Do I hold space to feel? To cry?
What steps can I take to hold myself and my emotions more and start living more in alignment with my heart?

node.text:
Sirius Gateway ◦ July 3 - 7
These last few days you may have been feeling a little unsettled, sleepy, uncertain or fatigued. This has been because we’ve been entering the rising of the spiritual sun Sirius, with tomorrow as the sun hits 14° being the peak for this gateway. 

Sirius is a fixed star that resides in the sign of Cancer. Ancients have long believed that the Sirius Star is the gateway to the spirit realm and has been said to be the brightest star in the nights sky from earths perspective. This time is known as the opening of the portal and the wisdom of the spiritual realm, a time where we can connect with higher beings and ask for their wisdom and guidance for our souls here on earth. 
⁣
This portal opens to awaken us and bring our consciousness to another level. Messages from spirit guides may come through to you in dreams or visions if you are in tune and open with receiving messages. If not you can use practices such as meditating or journaling with the intention to connect to your guides and letting whatever messages come through flow onto the paper. 

If you have any personal planets that are in Cancer at 14° than you are more aligned and in tune with the magic of Sirius and this time is even more magical for you.

Moon in Taurus conjunct Uranus ◦
Uranus is our planet of awakenings, bringing with it lots of realisations. Taurus represents comfort and stability, this conjunction is asking you to reflect on what you think you need to feel secure and what “things” you hold your value and your self worth onto. 

Today’s journal prompt:
What is a view of myself that I need to let go of?

Beautiful art by @lilly_prinz

node.text:
We currently have Mars, Saturn and Uranus making a T-Square aspect to one another. While Saturn and Uranus have been square for a while now, these are slow moving planets, which means their effects and influences are more subtle than our fast moving planets. So when Mars comes in to play this heightens the influence and guides you towards some major break throughs within your life. 

Ultimately this T-Square is here to guide you towards feeling empowered in who you are and in the direction you are going, this is the time to take action and take charge of the path you are heading. 

You are the author of your story, what chapter are you going to write next?

Also the intense and aggressive Mars energy is strong over this next week, be sure to prioritise your self care and set healthy boundaries with yourself and those around you.

node.text:
Neptune our planet of spirituality stationed retrograde yesterday and will be up until mid November. 

This retrograde is extremely important for your spiritual wellbeing. Neptune brings us this mystical healing energy. She is a very slow moving planet, who likes to hide behind the scenes. 

When Neptune goes retrograde things that have been going on in the shadows begin to come to the surface and those perfect illusions start to crumble around you. This retrograde is very much the reality check that you need. Here to wake you up to what’s really been happening around you. 

Neptune retrograde is here to guide you to stop making excuses and living in your own fantasy world, so that you can make positive changes to move forward. 

This retrograde also heightens your dreams, which means during this time you are likely to dream more and for those dreams to be extremely vivid and clear. Keep a dream journal and write down all things and feelings that come through in your dreams as soon as you wake up.

node.text:
Full Moon in Capricorn ◦ Thursday, June 24
This Full Moon resurfaces and shines light on your karmic patterns and guides you towards a shift to dive deeper into your purpose here on earth. You may feel after this Full Moon like your perspective on who you are or what you want for your life has shifted. 

Full Moons happen towards the end of the lunar cycle, signifying an end of something within your life, closing the chapter. This Full Moon is the time to close the chapters of doubt and unproductive cycles and habits. 

Ritual for Capricorn Full Moon:
Set up your space, light some candles, place your favourite crystals in your palm or by you. Take a deep breath in and call in the energy of the moon. 

Write down all of the unproductive habits and doubts that you are wanting to let go of. 

As Capricorn is an earth sign, an earthing release is a really powerful ritual for this Full Moon. Bury your paper of things you are releasing into the ground, or in a pot plant, using the element of earth to hold you as you release. As you shovel the dirt or sand over your paper, begin to envision all those things that you wrote down releasing from your body.

#fullmoonincapricorn #earthmoonawakening
